{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: three source clients -> aggregation/orchestration -> summary input payload. MOCK-MISS: this is not a single pure function unless all source wiring is bypassed. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network is required to prove inclusion; in-process fakes for each source can reproduce missing-source wiring bugs. LLM-DEP: assertion is about input payload composition, not model output quality. REJECTION-GATE: System was considered and rejected because behavior text only requires that data is passed, not that real endpoints are contacted.","test_description":"Wire the real orchestrator with three stub source adapters returning distinct sentinel fields; run report generation up to the summary-call boundary and assert the exact payload sent to summary generation contains all three sentinels.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears when collector error handling and report assembly interact. MOCK-MISS: unit tests of a formatter alone miss orchestration behavior (continue vs abort). REAL-INFRA: a stubbed source throwing timeout/exception is sufficient; no real network outage is required. LLM-DEP: correctness is fallback control flow and section marker, not model judgment. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected because behavior text does not require validating real network failure mechanics, only graceful degradation behavior.","test_description":"Run the report pipeline with two normal source stubs and one failing stub; assert process completes, output includes `data unavailable` for the failed section, and other sections are still populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This behavior is about summary faithfulness/accuracy, which depends on real model output quality. MOCK-HIDE/LLM-DEP: deterministic stubs always pass and cannot detect hallucination, omission, or misstatement of key values. MULTI-STEP: single model decision point, so not Workflow. REJECTION-GATE: Integration rejected because behavior text requires semantic accuracy of generated narrative, not just routing/payload formatting.","test_description":"Use representative real input datasets with known key values, invoke the real summary-generation model, and evaluate whether the produced narrative preserves those values (allowing wording variation but not factual drift) across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly spans end-to-end external interactions (source APIs + email delivery/inbox). REAL-INFRA: requires real HTTP/API/email transport behavior; in-process fakes can hide auth, transport, formatting, or provider acceptance failures. LLM-DEP: this behavior can be validated on delivery correctness without requiring judgment about model quality. REJECTION-GATE: Agentic considered but rejected because behavior text focuses on inbox delivery of complete report, not evaluating semantic quality of model output.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled pipeline in a system test environment against real reachable endpoints (or production-like test services) and a real test mailbox; assert message is delivered to configured recipients with expected report sections and attachments/body structure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.17,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is orchestration across modules: delivery failure handling, persistence, and next-run retry logic. Integration level includes local filesystem and module wiring. REAL-INFRA: real OS/network is not strictly required; a delivery adapter stub that raises unreachable plus temp local filesystem can expose logic bugs. MULTI-STEP: two runs, but not multiple agentic decisions. REJECTION-GATE: System rejected because behavior text does not require proving real SMTP/network failure modes, only fallback persistence and retry semantics.","test_description":"Run cycle 1 with a failing email adapter and temp filesystem; assert report is persisted locally. Run cycle 2 with email adapter restored; assert persisted report is retried/sent and local pending file is cleared or marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
